// Accuracy: 97.5%
//
// SHADOW CANDIDATE - deployed INERT (trigger: manual) so it ships to praxisbot via the normal
// praxis/ sync but NEVER serves live traffic. Loaded into the shadow holder (ShadowProcedures)
// at startup, separate from the live ReactiveRegistry. Numeric evaluation of the evolved network
// lives in pares-umbra (the arena), per C-PLURES - pares-radix only LOADS this candidate and
// (later) evaluates/promotes it once it consistently beats the live classifier.
// See praxis/shadow/README.md.
//
// NOTE: pares-radix's .px engine (pluresdb-px) does NOT parse umbra's brace-block dialect
// (verified). The original evolved source is preserved verbatim in the EVOLVED-SOURCE block at
// the bottom (each line //-prefixed) for provenance / re-evolution. The executable procedure
// below is the loadable, manual-trigger pares-radix form; it routes through the umbra-backed
// evaluate_shadow_classifier action carrying model id "route_message".

procedure shadow_route_message:
  trigger: manual
  given: "Umbra-evolved router candidate (97.5%). Shadow-only; never serves live output."
  extract_features {content: $content} -> $features
  evaluate_shadow_classifier {model: "route_message", features: $features} -> $result
  emit {shadow: "route_message", result: $result}

